  "Infra and DevOps/D2/stack-run-d2-demo.md": "# Stack Run ‚Äî D2 Job Processor Demo\n\n> Generated by `docker-compose-stack-agent` v1.0  \n> Task root: `tasks/Infra and DevOps/D2` ¬∑ Base SHA: `no-git`\n\n## Table of contents\n\n1. [Execution Summary](#execution-summary)\n2. [Stack Layout](#stack-layout)\n3. [Docker Compose and Dockerfiles](#docker-compose-and-dockerfiles)\n4. [Seed and Fixtures](#seed-and-fixtures)\n5. [One-Command E2E](#one-command-e2e)\n6. [Inter-Service Log Proof](#inter-service-log-proof)\n7. [Teardown and Re-up](#teardown-and-re-up)\n8. [Quick Reference](#quick-reference)\n\n---\n\n## Execution Summary\n\n```yaml\nagent: docker-compose-stack-agent\nversion: 1.0\ntask_root: tasks/Infra and DevOps/D2\nrun_base_sha: no-git\nstack_name: d2-job-stack\nservices: [db, api, worker]\napi_port: 8080\ne2e_command: ./scripts/run-e2e.sh\ne2e_result: 0  # 3 passed (2026-06-23) ‚Äî proof: proof/e2e-tests-all-green.txt\nteardown_command: ./scripts/stack-down.sh\nreup_e2e_result: 0  # 3 passed after down -v + stack-up ‚Äî proof: proof/teardown-and-fresh-reup.txt\nresult: pass  # E2E green, inter-service logs captured, teardown/re-up verified\n```\n\n**Proof artifacts:** `proof/e2e-tests-all-green.txt`, `proof/service-interaction-logs.txt`, `proof/teardown-and-fresh-reup.txt`\n\n**Environment note:** Colima Docker (2026-06-23). Initial `docker pull postgres:16-alpine` failed with Colima VM TLS (`x509: certificate signed by unknown authority`); image was sideloaded via `crane pull` + `docker load` on the host (macOS trust store). Stack unchanged; all E2E and re-up runs passed with 3/3 pytest green.\n\n### Summary\n\n| item | value |\n|---|---|\n| Stack | FastAPI API + PostgreSQL + Python worker |\n| One-command test | `./scripts/run-e2e.sh` |\n| Teardown | `./scripts/stack-down.sh` (`compose down -v`) |\n| Re-up | `./scripts/stack-up.sh && ./scripts/run-e2e.sh` |\n\n---\n\n## Stack Layout\n\n```\nD2/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose-stack-agent.md  # agent spec (docker-compose-stack-agent)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ api/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requirements.txt\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ app/\n‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py          # POST/GET jobs, health\n‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ db.py\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ worker/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requirements.txt\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ worker.py            # polls pending jobs, uppercases payload\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ db/init/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 01-schema.sql\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ 02-seed.sql\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ scripts/\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ stack-up.sh\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ stack-down.sh\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ run-e2e.sh\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tests/\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ requirements.txt\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ test_e2e.py\n```\n\n---\n\n## Docker Compose and Dockerfiles\n\n### docker-compose.yml\n\n```yaml\nname: d2-job-stack\n\nservices:\n  db:\n    image: postgres:16-alpine\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_DB: jobs\n      POSTGRES_USER: jobs\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: jobs\n    volumes:\n      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n      - ./db/init:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d:ro\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD-SHELL\", \"pg_isready -U jobs -d jobs\"]\n      interval: 5s\n      timeout: 3s\n      retries: 10\n      start_period: 5s\n\n  api:\n    build:\n      context: ./api\n    environment:\n      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://jobs:jobs@db:5432/jobs\n      LOG_LEVEL: info\n    ports:\n      - \"${API_PORT:-8080}:8080\"\n    depends_on:\n      db:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD\", \"python\", \"-c\", \"import urllib.request; urllib.request.urlopen('http://127.0.0.1:8080/health')\"]\n      interval: 10s\n      timeout: 3s\n      retries: 6\n      start_period: 10s\n\n  worker:\n    build:\n      context: ./worker\n    environment:\n      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://jobs:jobs@db:5432/jobs\n      WORKER_POLL_SECONDS: \"2\"\n      LOG_LEVEL: info\n    depends_on:\n      db:\n        condition: service_healthy\n      api:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\nvolumes:\n  pgdata:\n```\n\n### api/Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.12-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \\\n    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \\\n    PORT=8080\n\nRUN adduser --disabled-password --gecos \"\" appuser\n\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\nCOPY app ./app\n\nUSER appuser\n\nEXPOSE 8080\n\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=10s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD python -c \"import urllib.request; urllib.request.urlopen('http://127.0.0.1:8080/health')\" || exit 1\n\nCMD [\"uvicorn\", \"app.main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"8080\"]\n```\n\n### worker/Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.12-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \\\n    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1\n\nRUN adduser --disabled-password --gecos \"\" appuser\n\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\nCOPY worker.py .\n\nUSER appuser\n\nCMD [\"python\", \"worker.py\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Seed and Fixtures\n\n| file | purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `db/init/01-schema.sql` | `jobs` table + status index |\n| `db/init/02-seed.sql` | inserts `seed-welcome` row (`done`, uppercase result) |\n\nSeed runs automatically on **first** Postgres volume mount via `/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/`. After `./scripts/stack-down.sh` (`down -v`), the next `stack-up.sh` recreates the volume and re-applies init scripts.\n\nE2E test `test_seeded_job_readable` calls `GET /jobs/seeded` to prove seed data is present.\n\n---\n\n## One-Command E2E\n\n### Command\n\n```bash\ncd \"tasks/Infra and DevOps/D2\"\nchmod +x scripts/*.sh\n./scripts/run-e2e.sh\n```\n\n### Output (actual ‚Äî 2026-06-23, all green)\n\nSee full capture in `proof/e2e-tests-all-green.txt`. Summary:\n\n```text\n==> ensure stack is up\n==> docker compose up --build -d\n...\napi healthy\n==> run e2e tests against http://127.0.0.1:8080\ntests/test_e2e.py::test_health PASSED\ntests/test_e2e.py::test_seeded_job_readable PASSED\ntests/test_e2e.py::test_api_worker_pipeline PASSED\n============================== 3 passed in 1.46s ===============================\nAll E2E checks passed.\n```\n\nExit code: **0**\n\n---\n\n## Inter-Service Log Proof\n\nCaptured in `proof/service-interaction-logs.txt` (2026-06-23):\n\n| step | service | log excerpt (actual) |\n|---|---|---|\n| ingest | api | `INFO [api] created job job-c566a81f0f83 status=pending payload='docker compose e2e'` |\n| poll | worker | `INFO [worker] processing job job-c566a81f0f83` |\n| complete | worker | `INFO [worker] completed job job-c566a81f0f83 result='DOCKER COMPOSE E2E'` |\n| read | api | `INFO [api] GET /jobs/job-c566a81f0f83 status=done` |\n| seed proof | api | E2E hits `/jobs/seeded` ‚Üí `seed-welcome` / `done` |\n\nCollect live excerpts:\n\n```bash\ndocker compose logs --no-color api worker | grep -E 'created job|processing job|completed job|GET /jobs'\n```\n\n---\n\n## Teardown and Re-up\n\n### Teardown\n\n```bash\n./scripts/stack-down.sh\n```\n\nRemoves containers **and** the `pgdata` volume (`docker compose down -v`).\n\n### Re-up from zero + E2E\n\n```bash\n./scripts/stack-down.sh\n./scripts/stack-up.sh\n./scripts/run-e2e.sh\n```\n\nSecond E2E run must pass again (fresh DB, seed re-applied, worker processes new job).\n\n**Verified 2026-06-23** ‚Äî see `proof/teardown-and-fresh-reup.txt`: `stack-down` exit 0, `stack-up` exit 0, second `./scripts/run-e2e.sh` exit 0 (3 passed in 2.51s).\n\n---\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n| action | command |\n|---|---|\n| up | `./scripts/stack-up.sh` |\n| test | `./scripts/run-e2e.sh` |\n| logs | `docker compose logs -f api worker db` |\n| down | `./scripts/stack-down.sh` |\n| clean re-up + E2E | `./scripts/stack-down.sh && ./scripts/stack-up.sh && ./scripts/run-e2e.sh` |\n",
